A 15-year-old boy has been arrested on suspicion of attempted murder after another boy the same age was stabbed on a double decker bus.

It is believed the teenage victim was injured during a fight on board a 151 bus in Sutton, south-west London, at around 2.30pm yesterday.

He reportedly got off the bus near the Rose Hill roundabout and walked around 250 yards before collapsing outside a KFC takeaway on St Helier Avenue.

